ğŸ‘‰Problem 2ï¸âƒ£: African Cities
ğŸ“š Problem:
Given the CITY and COUNTRY tables, query the names of all cities where the CONTINENT is â€˜Africaâ€™.
Note: CITY.CountryCode and COUNTRY.Code are matching key columns.

ğŸ‘‰SOLUTION:MYSQL
-----------------
SELECT 
    c.NAME 
FROM 
    CITY c
JOIN 
    COUNTRY co
ON 
    c.COUNTRYCODE = co.CODE
WHERE 
    co.CONTINENT = 'Africa';


---------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ‘‰Problem 3ï¸âƒ£: Average Population of Each Continent
ğŸ“š Problem:
Given the CITY and COUNTRY tables, query the names of all the continents (COUNTRY.Continent) and
their respective average city populations (CITY.Population) rounded down to the nearest integer.
Note: CITY.CountryCode and COUNTRY.Code are matching key columns

ğŸ‘‰SOLUTION:MYSQL
-----------------
SELECT 
    co.CONTINENT, 
    FLOOR(AVG(c.POPULATION)) AS avg_city_population
FROM 
    CITY c
JOIN 
    COUNTRY co
ON 
    c.COUNTRYCODE = co.CODE
GROUP BY 
    co.CONTINENT;






